        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "QoIs are explicitly referenced in the device design specification and linked to acceptance thresholds; traceability matrix entry reviewed and approved by lead design engineer."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the same TKA implant geometry (production CAD revision D), the same UHMWPE grade (GUR 1050), and loading conditions within the defined operating envelope. Cadaveric specimens spanned the target patient weight range (68–102 kg). The validation domain overlaps the COU domain for all primary input parameters; any extrapolation is minor and bounded by the sensitivity analysis results.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/tka-validation-relevance-ac-07",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Validation geometry, material, and loading conditions all within the COU operating envelope; domain overlap documented in the validation relevance matrix with no primary parameter requiring extrapolation > 10% beyond validation range."
      }
    },
    {
