      "rationale": "Six cadaveric knee specimens were used for validation, spanning the target patient weight and demographic range. All specimens were from donors aged 55–75 years with no prior knee surgery or diagnosed osteoarthritis beyond Grade II. Specimen preparation and implantation followed a standardised surgical protocol performed by a single orthopaedic surgeon. Specimen-to-specimen variability in contact pressure measurements characterised and incorporated into the experimental uncertainty bounds.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/tka-test-samples-ac-12",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Minimum 5 cadaveric specimens spanning the target patient weight range; standardised implantation protocol; specimen selection criteria documented and approved by study protocol."
      }
