      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency assessment was conducted mapping all experimental input parameters to their COU counterparts. Loading magnitude, flexion angle range, insert geometry, material grade, and contact pair definition were all confirmed equivalent between validation and COU contexts. The only noted difference — use of cadaveric soft tissue constraints versus the kinematic boundary conditions in the COU model — was assessed via a sensitivity run showing < 3% effect on peak contact stress, within the established model uncertainty band.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
